  "name": "RPlog_Tea_for_Three",
  "title": "Skeletons Over Tea",
  "summary": "In the spartan base housing assigned to the Delgard women, the New Republic Captain Rasi pays a call on the recovering ambassador Ambrosia Delgard, who is tinkering with a droid hand-brace to steady her trembling, brain-damaged left hand. After Rasi gives Ambrosia's traumatized daughter Gabi a toy and promises a gunnery sim program, the adults settle to tea and a guarded political conversation. Ambrosia presses Rasi about the 'tainted' Imperial humanitarian shipment to Caspar that framed her and damaged Republic-CDU relations, while he argues the Empire alone bears the blame for the war. The talk turns deeply personal and off the record as Ambrosia confides the secret of Dr. Liora Kovani, the daughter taken from her decades ago when she was an Imperial slave carrying Moff Tyruni's child, now an Imperial-raised physician she encountered during her captivity under Lord Thel and persuaded to leave the Empire. Ambrosia recounts her own journey from slave to Republic diplomat and extracts Rasi's agreement to keep her origins and Gabi's unknown sister strictly confidential as Gabi bursts in seeking help modifying her new toy.",
